@page
@model BrainStormEra.Views.Course.ReviewCourseModel
@{
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>C++ Programming Full Course</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@300;400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.4/css/all.min.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/Course/ReviewCourse.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/base.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/HomePage/landing_page.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="~/lib/img/BrainStormEra_logo.png" type="image/x-icon">

</head>
<body>

    @await Html.PartialAsync("~/Views/Shared/Instructor/Header/_Header.cshtml")

    <div class="header">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row py-5">
                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <h1 class="display-4">C++ Programming Full Course</h1>
                    <p class="lead">The course provides a solid foundation in C++ for beginners, helping them develop basic programming skills and apply them to real projects.</p>

                    <div class="d-flex mb-2 mt-5">
                        <h3 class="price  "> $199.99</h3>

                    </div>

                    <div class="d-flex mb-4 mt-2">
                        <button class="btn btn-success me-3">Enroll</button>

                    </div>
                    <div class="d-flex text-white mt-3">
                        <div class="me-4"><i class="fas fa-clock me-2"></i>30 hours</div>
                        <div class="me-4"><i class="fas fa-book me-2"></i>125 lessons</div>
                        <div class="me-4"><i class="fas fa-users me-2"></i>120 learners</div>
                        <div class="me-4"><i class="fas fa-certificate me-2"></i>Certificate</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <img src="/assests/img/img_course.png" alt="C++ Logo" class="img-fluid">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <nav class="nav nav-pills nav-fill mb-4">
            <a class="nav-link active" href="#introduction">Introduction</a>
            <a class="nav-link" href="#curriculum">Curriculum</a>
            <a class="nav-link" href="#certificate">Certificate</a>
        </nav>

        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>C++ is one of the most popular programming languages, especially in competitive programming. Currently, most young people prioritize learning C++ to build a foundation and programming mindset when first starting to explore programming. The basic C++ course is designed with the most basic and easy-to-understand knowledge to help you access it easily.</p>
                <h2 id="introduction">Course goal:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Helps you learn C++ from scratch quickly and easily.</li>
                    <li>Equips you with the necessary knowledge and skills to write simple C++ programs.</li>
                    <li>Helps you understand and use important concepts in C++.</li>
                    <li>Creates a foundation for you to self-study and develop more complex C++ programs.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 id="curriculum">Target audience:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>This course is for beginners who have absolutely no programming knowledge, or those who have lost the basics and want to regain basic programming knowledge, specifically C++.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 id="certificate">Teaching method:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>The course combines theory and practice.</li>
                    <li>Students will learn through video lectures, theoretical readings, practice exercises, and theory tests.</li>
                    <li>Students will be able to ask and answer questions directly with their classmates and the course manager.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="learning-outcome">
                    <h2>What will you learn?</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>After completing the course, students will have enough knowledge and skills to write simple C++ programs.</li>
                        <li>Students will understand and use important concepts in C++ easily.</li>
                        <li>Students will have a solid foundation to self-study and develop more complex C++ programs.</li>
                        <li>The course will help students improve their logical thinking, problem-solving, and programming skills effectively.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3>Course Content</h3>
                <p>36 Chapters • 125 Lectures • 30 hours and 40 minutes</p>
                <div class="accordion" id="courseContentAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                                Part 1: Overview of C++ Programming
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#courseContentAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <a href="lesson1.html" target="_blank">Lesson 1: Introduction to C++ (5 minutes)</a>
                                <a href="lesson2.html" target="_blank">Lesson 2: Variables and Data Types (10 minutes)</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                                Part 2: Functions and Control Flow
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#courseContentAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <a href="lesson3.html" target="_blank">Lesson 1: Functions in C++ (15 minutes)</a>
                                <a href="lesson4.html" target="_blank">Lesson 2: Control Structures (20 minutes)</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                                Part 3: Object-Oriented Programming
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#courseContentAccordion">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <a href="lesson5.html" target="_blank">Lesson 1: Classes and Objects (25 minutes)</a>
                                <a href="lesson6.html" target="_blank">Lesson 2: Inheritance and Polymorphism (30 minutes)</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="approval-buttons">
            <button class="btn btn-success">Approve</button>
            <button class="btn btn-danger">Decline</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    </div>

    @await Html.PartialAsync("~/Views/Shared/Footer/_Footer.cshtml")

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script src="~/js/Course/ReviewCourse.js"></script>
</body>
</html>